The Nigerian Meteorological Agency (NiMet) has predicted thundary, rainy activities across the country for Wednesday. NiMet’s weather outlook on Tuesday in Abuja predicted thunderstorms over Kano and Katsina of the Northern States in the morning hours. It predicted thunderstorm over Kano, Katsina, Potiskum, Damaturu, Dutse and Gusau later in the day with day and night temperatures of 30 to 34 degree Celsius and 23 to 26 degree Celsius respectively. ” For Central States, partly cloudy to cloudy condition is anticipated over the region in the morning hours. ” There are prospects of thunderstorms over Jos, Gombe, Yola, Mambila Plateau and Bauchi during the afternoon/evening hours. “Day and night temperature values are expected to be 28 to 34 degree Celsius and 18 to 24 degree Celsius respectively, ” NiMet said . According to it, cloudy conditions are expected over the Southern States with chances of rain over Warri, Benin and Asaba axis in the morning. The agency predicted intermittent rains over most places in the region later in the day with day and night temperatures of 29 to 32 degree Celsius and 21 to 24 degree Celsius respectively. NAN 